It's taken me three decades to find spaghetti and meatballs like this. It smelled faintly of bell pepper or fennel, but the taste is sublime, with complex layers & depth of flavor. Reminded me of my early days in New Jersey. Real down-home Italian but cooked with finesse. You can't get sauce like this from a jar. Sauce tastes like love. Also can't say enough about the crisp chewy gooey goodness of their slices; some of the best around, and the most reasonably priced. Service was fast, efficient & warm. Beats anything you can get anywhere else. I'm looking at you, Manhattan.

Fresh, quality ingredients set this local favorite apart. The homemade tomato sauce, chicken Parmesan, and shrimp Alfredo make repeat customers out of the local precinct, fire house, and long-time residents. Proudly run by Italian-Americans, take a right at the Italian flag waving over Lorimer Street to get a taste of one of the best slices in Brooklyn.

Like the other reviewers say, this is a good old-fashioned pizza place. Everything is terrific and, best of all, the owners are friendly and real.  Love love love the salad pizza, which seems a healthy option to regular pizza:  it's a baked crust with sauce and then a nice arugula salad on top.  Mmm . . . getting hungry thinking about it.  Definitely the best pizza joint in East Williamsburg (though Carmine's on Graham is close).
